2026-05-17 17:51:12 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #7 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"code": "# intent: Compute state-level proportion of 'generally unsafe' AQI days for 2024 from the county-level file, merge with Wildfire_Acres_by_State.csv (Total Acres Burned for 2024), then compute Pearson correlation between proportion and acres. Round correlation to 2 decimals and print it.\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom scipy.stats import pearsonr\nimport numpy as np\n\n# Load files using path map\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json\nmanifest_path = Path('DOWNLOAD_MANIFEST_PATH')\n# But manifest path variable isn't provided; use environment method from tools: use explicit paths from download output\n\n# Direct local paths from the download step\naqi_path = '/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1728690_1779040244353/kramabench-wildfire-hard-14/files/annual_aqi_by_county_2024.csv'\nfire_path = '/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1728690_1779040244353/kramabench-wildfire-hard-14/files/Wildfire_Acres_by_State.csv'\n\n# Read AQI CSV\naqi = pd.read_csv(aqi_path)\n# Clean column names (strip quotes/spaces)\naqi.columns = [c.strip().strip('\"') for c in aqi.columns]\n# Inspect relevant columns\nprint('AQI columns:', aqi.columns.tolist())\nprint(aqi.head(3).to_string(index=False))\n\n# Define generally unsafe as Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups, Unhealthy, Very Unhealthy, Hazardous days sum\n# Some counties have 'Days with AQI' less than 365 if monitoring days differ; use sum of those unsafe category days divided by Days with AQI to get proportion per county, then compute state-level weighted proportion by summing unsafe days and total days across counties.\nunsafe_cols = ['Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups Days','Unhealthy Days','Very Unhealthy Days','Hazardous Days']\nfor col in unsafe_cols:\n    if col not in aqi.columns:\n        print('Missing column', col)\n\n# C